# {{EXTENSION_NAME}}

An [Asyar](https://github.com/Xoshbin/asyar) extension.

## Development

```bash
pnpm install      # install dependencies
pnpm run build    # production build
pnpm run dev      # watch mode (hot reload)
```

Once built, register the extension for dev loading:

```bash
asyar attach .
```

Validate your manifest before publishing:

```bash
asyar validate
```

## Publishing

```bash
asyar publish
```

## Key manifest fields

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| `asyarSdk` | Minimum SDK version required (semver range, e.g. `"^1.3.4"`) |
| `minAppVersion` | Minimum Asyar app version required (semver, e.g. `"0.1.0"`) |
| `platforms` | Restrict to specific OSes. Omit for universal. Valid values: `"macos"`, `"windows"`, `"linux"` |
| `permissions` | Declare every permission your extension uses (see [docs](https://github.com/Xoshbin/asyar/blob/main/docs/extension-development.md#10-permissions-reference)) |

### Platform example

If your extension only works on macOS and Linux, add to `manifest.json`:

```json
"platforms": ["macos", "linux"]
```

Leave the field out entirely if your extension works on all platforms.
